entities.name: ElizaOS
entities.description: A modular and collaborative framework with a focus on AI agents and decentralized systems. It aims to provide a stable platform and enhance developer experience.

entities.name: ai16z
entities.description: An older token, the predecessor to ElizaOS tokens, which is currently undergoing a migration process. Further details about its specific characteristics or origins are not provided.

entities.name: Kraken
entities.description: A cryptocurrency exchange platform that facilitates the trading and management of digital assets. It is currently involved in the migration process of ai16z tokens to ElizaOS.

entities.name: Anthropic
entities.description: An AI safety and research company developing large language models. Known for its AI models, including 'Sonnet 4.0'.

entities.name: Sonnet 4.0
entities.description: A specific large language model developed by Anthropic. It was identified as having an issue with improperly closing XML tags.

entities.name: Babylon
entities.description: A project related to the ElizaOS ecosystem, with discussions around its waitlist and potential token strategy. Its exact nature and tokenomics are being clarified.

entities.name: Ethereum
entities.description: A decentralized, open-source blockchain system that features smart contract functionality. It is a major platform in the cryptocurrency and blockchain space.

entities.name: Vitalik Buterin
entities.description: A prominent figure in the Ethereum ecosystem, co-founder of Ethereum. He is associated with discussions and attention towards new projects within the ecosystem.

entities.name: Davide
entities.description: A figure from the Ethereum Foundation (EF) involved in ecosystem discussions. His role is related to advancing development and strategic partnerships within the broader Ethereum space.

entities.name: Tina
entities.description: A contributor from Flashbots, an organization focused on Ethereum research and development, particularly around MEV (Maximal Extractable Value). She is involved in discussions about new games and ecosystem expansion.

entities.name: Flashbots
entities.description: An organization that focuses on research and development within the Ethereum ecosystem, particularly concerning MEV. It plays a role in the advancement of blockchain technology and its applications.

entities.name: LangChain
entities.description: A framework for developing applications powered by language models. The ElizaOS core system was migrated away from an older version (v0.3) of this dependency.

entities.name: OpenRouter
entities.description: A plugin within the ElizaOS ecosystem that provides access to various language models. Documentation for its text embedding feature has been published to improve developer accessibility.

entities.name: DeepSeek API
entities.description: An API integration that was discussed for addition to the ElizaOS ecosystem. It represents a feature request for extending the platform's capabilities.

entities.name: Farcaster
entities.description: A decentralized social network protocol. Support for Farcaster applications was identified as a feature request for the ElizaOS roadmap.

entities.name: Base
entities.description: A Layer 2 scaling solution for Ethereum, developed by Coinbase. Integration requests for applications built on Base were noted for the ElizaOS roadmap.

entities.name: Discord
entities.description: A communication platform widely used by online communities for voice, video, and text chat. It hosts discussions and development updates for projects like ElizaOS.

entities.name: GitHub
entities.description: A web-based platform for version control using Git. It is used for hosting, collaborating on, and managing software development projects, including those of ElizaOS.
